[h1]LxC - Build Everywhere[/h1]

Allows building on terrain that normally doesn't support it.

[h2]What it does[/h2]
Adds construction affordances (Light, Medium, Heavy, Diggable) to terrain types that normally block building:

[list]
[*] [b]Shallow water[/b] (fresh, ocean, and moving)
[*] [b]Chest-deep water[/b] (moving)
[*] [b]Marsh[/b]
[*] [b]Marshy soil[/b] (adds Medium + Heavy -- already supports Light structures)
[*] [b]Soft sand[/b] (adds Medium + Heavy -- already supports Light structures)
[*] [b]Mud[/b]
[/list]

You can now place walls, floors, furniture, workbenches, and other structures on these tiles.

[h2]How it works[/h2]
Pure XML patches -- no C# code, no Harmony. Maximum compatibility with other mods.

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
[list]
[*] RimWorld 1.6
[*] Safe to add mid-save
[*] Compatible with all DLCs
[*] Uses XPath patches, so it works alongside other terrain mods
[/list]

[h2]Credits[/h2]
Original mod by [b]John Midnight[/b] ([url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1587651463]Build Everywhere[/url]).
Updated for RimWorld 1.6 by Lexxers.

